      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense from a climate perspective. but i keep hearing people say it's basically just a regressive tax that hits working-class people the hardest since they often have no choice but to drive. how do planners reconcile that tension if the policy is seen as a 'fundamental requirement'?",
