      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Planners generally reconcile this tension through robust revenue recycling and equity guardrails built into the policy design. Funds generated from the pricing are often earmarked for subsidizing public transit fares or improving underserved neighborhoods, directly offsetting the cost burden. Furthermore, exemptions or discounts are often implemented for low-income vehicles or essential workers to mitigate the regressive impact. This approach reframes the fee not just as a tax, but as a mechanism to fund systemic mobility improvements.",
